      No amalgamation for Amalgamated and Amalgamated
   =20
 =20
Look, I am sorry, but if you are a bank regulator and Amalgamated Bank come=
s to you and says =E2=80=9Cwe want to buy Amalgamated Bank of Chicago=E2=80=
=9D I think your duty is to:=09Be confused, for a bit, because why would Am=
algamated Bank need to buy Amalgamated Bank?=C2=A0=09Then, when you figure =
out what is going on, laugh for like 20 minutes?=09Absolutely approve the d=
eal, that=E2=80=99s the best merger ever, if Amalgamated Bank wants to amal=
gamate with Amalgamated Bank then you let them amalgamate it up, they were =
born to amalgamate, how can you stand in their way?=E2=80=9CThis is perfect=
,=E2=80=9D  I wrote when Amalgamated announced its amalgamation with Amalga=
mated,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Call mergers can stop now, they have done the best one.=
=E2=80=9D But=C2=A0no they have not:Amalgamated Financial Corp.=C2=A0(Nasda=
q: AMAL), the holding company for=C2=A0Amalgamated Bank=C2=A0(=E2=80=9CAMAL=
=E2=80=9D or the =E2=80=9CBank=E2=80=9D), America=E2=80=99s socially respon=
sible bank, [Friday] announced it has withdrawn its application for regulat=
ory approval to acquire=C2=A0Amalgamated Bank of Chicago=C2=A0(=E2=80=9CABO=
C=E2=80=9D) due to an inability to obtain such approval. As a result, AMAL =
is no longer proceeding with the transaction.I do not know what the regulat=
ory problem was, but I assume that it was just too much amalgamation. It so=
unds like an antitrust problem, when an Amalgamated Bank amalgamates with a=
n Amalgamated Bank, though as I  pointed out last time neither Amalgamated =
Bank nor Amalgamated Bank is particularly amalgamated. (Each is a bank foun=
ded by an amalgamated=C2=A0union,=C2=A0not an amalgamation=C2=A0of other ba=
nks.) Now they will not be an Amalgamated Amalgamated Bank.
