lid; background-color: #ccc;"> steal bribe money</a> from the alleged maste=
rmind of the looting, Malaysian financier Jho Low:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Malaysian financier Jho Low, the alleged architec=
t of the massive fraud, asked Leissner to =E2=80=9Chold=E2=80=9D 145 millio=
n euros ($162 million) in a shell company in Mauritius, Leissner saw an opp=
ortunity. Because much of his money was invested in illiquid assets, Leissn=
er told the jury he kept $80 million for himself.</p></blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He also stole money from Ng! Or, sorry, =E2=80=9Cborro=
wed=E2=80=9D it:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He said he the=
n borrowed another $1.25 million from Ng, his subordinate at Goldman.</p><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Leissner said his arrest in 2018 prevented him f=
rom repaying Ng any of the money. =E2=80=9CI had the intention to pay him b=
