.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Come on. I would let Ng go f=
ree and give him his $1.25 million back.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Al=
so here are some lazy euphemisms for bribery:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Leissner and Ng had code words for their kickbacks that they=
 would use on BlackBerry Messenger when they worried they might not get the=
 money, Leissner told the court.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI=
 think it was that the cakes or the cookies weren=E2=80=99t coming fast eno=
ugh,=E2=80=9D he said.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, o=
ne problem with raising $6 billion of bonds for a sovereign-backed developm=
ent fund and then stealing all the money is: How will the fund make interes=
t payments? In a sense that isn=E2=80=99t your problem =E2=80=94=C2=A0you a=
lready stole the money =E2=80=94=C2=A0but in a sense it is, because if the =
fund defaults on its first payment you are more likely to get caught:</p><b=
lockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Leissner testified to several instan=
ces when everything almost fell apart, including a moment in which 1MDB nea=
red a default when it missed its first interest payment on the Magnolia bon=
ds. The lapse tripped alarm bells within Goldman, Leissner said, and risked=
 triggering an investigation that would expose the whole scam.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For Goldman Sachs, a default by 1MDB would be =E2=80=
=9Ca reputational problem and money problem, because we had, of course, tak=
en $200 million out=E2=80=9D of the $1.75 billion. Personally, he said, he =
feared an investigation =E2=80=9Cwould uncover, in fact, one of the reasons=
 why there was no money left, which was the scheme.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess the lesson is that if you are going =
to steal all the money you raise in a bond deal, at least leave a few years=
 of coupons in an escrow account to cover your tracks? I don=E2=80=99t know=
, it doesn=E2=80=99t feel like a very good lesson.</p><table class=3D"heade=
